## Important Notes

- **Resource Structure**: this resource deploys boolean values for a group policy configuration. 
It has a hard dependency on the group policy configuration resource.
- **Authoring**: The policy name, class type, and category path must match what's defined in the Intune GUI. The Provider
will resolve the correct template and presentation IDs for you. The boolean values are stored as a set, so order is not significant.
- **Import ID Format**: When importing, use the composite ID format: `{groupPolicyConfigurationId}/definitionValues/{definitionValueId}`. 
The resource's `id` attribute is automatically set in this format during creation. During import, the provider will 
automatically resolve the policy metadata (policy_name, class_type, category_path) from the definition value instance ID.

