### Automated Import with PowerShell Helper Script

For simplified importing of existing boolean value configurations, use the included PowerShell script located at:
`scripts/powershell/device_management/Export-GroupPolicyBooleanValueToHCLForImport.ps1`

This script will:
- Connect to Microsoft Graph and retrieve your group policy configurations
- Identify all boolean value definitions in a selected configuration
- Generate ready-to-use Terraform import commands
- Generate complete HCL resource blocks with current values
- Save both to timestamped files for easy tracking

**Example Usage:**

```powershell
# Interactive mode - browse and select configuration
pwsh scripts/powershell/device_management/Export-GroupPolicyBooleanValueToHCLForImport.ps1 \
    -TenantId "your-tenant-id" \
    -ClientId "your-client-id" \
    -ClientSecret "your-client-secret" \
    -OutputDirectory "./imports"

# Direct mode - specify configuration ID
pwsh scripts/powershell/device_management/Export-GroupPolicyBooleanValueToHCLForImport.ps1 \
    -TenantId "your-tenant-id" \
    -ClientId "your-client-id" \
    -ClientSecret "your-client-secret" \
    -ConfigurationId "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-g7h8-i9j0-k1l2m3n4o5p6" \
    -OutputDirectory "./imports"
```

**Generated Output:**

The script generates two files:
1. `import_commands_[timestamp].sh` - Bash script with all import commands
2. `resources_[timestamp].tf` - Complete HCL resource definitions with current values

**Workflow:**

1. Run the script to generate import files
2. Review the generated HCL in `resources_[timestamp].tf`
3. Copy the resource definitions to your Terraform configuration
4. Update the `group_policy_configuration_id` references if needed
5. Run the import commands: `bash import_commands_[timestamp].sh`
6. Run `terraform plan` to verify the import was successful 